intro: Seseli triternatum, commonly known as three-parted seseli, is a flowering plant native to Europe and parts of Asia. It belongs to the family Apiaceae, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided leaves and small, clustered flowers. The plant typically grows in rocky or dry habitats and is known for its aromatic foliage. It produces small, white to greenish flowers that bloom in early summer. Seseli triternatum is often found in alpine and subalpine regions, where it thrives in well-drained soils.
